17.text: A snail and a slug lived near a small stream. They liked to play together in the school yard but little children screamed whenever they saw the snail and the slug. So they had to hide in the snow. “I’m sick of my shell”, said the snail to the slug. “With my shell stacked up on my back, I can never sprint.” “I wish I had a shell stuck on my back,” answered the slug. ‘Then I could go for a stroll on a snowy day and yet be warm and cozy.
